name: Abyssinian Erecta
description:
--Fig.19--
Abyssinian Erecta is a creature from Arber, an exoplanted located 407 light years away from Earth, orbiting the star Illirian.
The species grow in huge plantations and feed filtering dust particles from the sky. They have special bioluminescent fruit, that both attract species to polinize them and help other creatures to be guided in the dark.
Abyssinian can be grown inside buildings, and having them indoors means prosperity and abundance.
